Description: 2015 Fender 1957 Stratocaster Journeyman Relic Aged Blue Sparkle This is an exceptional guitar, the pickups are among the best I’ve ever owned. Hate to let this go, but I need to thin the herd. From Fender..... The Fender Custom Shop 1957 Relic Stratocaster takes you straight back to the pivotal year when the instrument was largely perfected into the form known worldwide today. Its deep-contoured alder body looks fantastic in Blue Sparkle! Sparkling tone comes from three hand-wound 50s Stratocaster single-coil pickups (reverse wound/reverse polarity middle pickup) with modern five-way switching. Other premium features include a 5/4 sawn maple neck with a 57 soft V profile and small headstock, 9.5-radius fingerboard with 21 narrow jumbo frets, single-ply pickguard, vintage white control knobs, American Vintage bridge, and American Vintage tuning machines. Includes hard-shell tweed case with gold interior. Title: 2015 Fender Custom Shop ‘57 Stratocaster Journeyman Relic Blue Sparkle
